  "text": "The Java class loading delegation chain in OpenJDK spans 5 key files:\n\n1. **ClassLoader.java** (line 534): `loadClass(String, boolean)` implements the classic parent-first delegation \u2014 checks `findLoadedClass()`, delegates to `parent.loadClass()` (or `findBootstrapClassOrNull()` if parent is null), then falls back to `findClass()`.\n\n2. **BuiltinClassLoader.java** (line 89, method at line 575): Overrides `loadClass` and delegates to `loadClassOrNull(String, boolean)` (line 589) which uses module-aware delegation: first checks if the class's package belongs to a module defined to a specific loader, delegates to that loader, otherwise falls back to parent delegation and classpath search.\n\n3. **ClassLoaders.java** (line 45): Defines the three built-in loaders as inner classes \u2014 `BootClassLoader` (line 131), `PlatformClassLoader` (line 146), and `AppClassLoader` (line 161) \u2014 all extending `BuiltinClassLoader`. The static initializer (line 63) creates the hierarchy: BOOT_LOADER \u2192 PLATFORM_LOADER(parent=BOOT) \u2192 APP_LOADER(parent=PLATFORM).\n\n4. **classLoader.cpp** (line 1141): `ClassLoader::load_class(Symbol*, PackageEntry*, bool, TRAPS)` is the native C++ implementation that searches the boot classpath (jimage and appended entries) to load class bytes.\n\n5. **systemDictionary.cpp** (line 574): `SystemDictionary::resolve_instance_class_or_null` is the central C++ entry point for class resolution \u2014 it checks the per-loader Dictionary cache first (line 590), then calls `load_instance_class` (line 1325) which either loads from shared archive or calls back into Java's `ClassLoader.loadClass()` for non-bootstrap loaders, and `ClassLoader::load_class` for bootstrap loading. `define_instance_class` (line 1364) and `update_dictionary` (line 1664) handle caching loaded classes.",
